
[1]shin

   SHIN, n. The fore part of the leg, particularly of the human leg; the
   fore part of the crural bone, called tibia. This bone being only
   covered by the skin, may be named for that circumstance; skin-bone; or
   it may be formed from the root of chine, edge.
